headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 13 of his 28 points in a decisive first quarter, and the Utah Jazz held on for a 96-86 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Early hole too big for Pistons; Jazz prevail 96-86

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored a season-high 35 points, going over 10,000 in his career, and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied to beat the Chicago Bulls 130-127 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard reaches 10,000 points; Clippers beat Bulls 130-127

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder to a 129-116 win over the Brooklyn Nets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: OKC burns the Nets behind Gilgeous-Alexander, five others.

events.name: Denver Nuggets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 22 points, 10 rebounds and five assists in another short night, and the Denver Nuggets reached .500 for the first time this season with a 114-89 victory over the New York Knicks on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Nuggets win easily again, rout Knicks 114-89

headlines.description: Sunday’s game between Boston and Miami was postponed because of contact tracing concerns within the Heat, a person familiar with the situation told The Associated Press.
headlines.shortLinkText: AP source: Celtics-Heat game postponed over virus concerns

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 27 points, LeBron James added 18 and the Los Angeles Lakers won for the sixth time in seven games with a 120-102 victory over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis has 27 as Lakers roll to 120-102 win over Rockets

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell had 27 points, five rebounds and five assists as the Minnesota Timberwolves snapped a seven-game losing streak with a 96-88 win Sunday over the San Antonio Spurs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell, Timberwolves snap 7-game skid with win over Spurs

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Damion Lee converted the tying and go-ahead free throws with 3.3 seconds left and the Golden State Warriors withstood a rough fourth quarter to hold off the Toronto Raptors 106-105 on Sunday night despite uncharacteristic struggles by Stephen Curry.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors hold off Raptors 106-105 on off night by Curry
